# Cursor Performance Optimization Rules

# Disable heavy AI features when not needed
- Disable AI chat when working on large files
- Limit AI completions to essential suggestions only
- Use AI features sparingly during heavy development

# File size limits for AI processing
- Files larger than 1000 lines should have AI features disabled
- Large JSON files should be excluded from AI indexing
- Binary files should never be processed by AI

# Performance guidelines
- Keep workspace clean and organized
- Close unused files and tabs
- Restart Cursor if performance degrades
- Monitor system resources during development

# Recommended extensions for performance
- Essential: ESLint, Prettier, GitLens
- Avoid: Multiple language servers, heavy syntax highlighters
- Disable: Unused extensions and experimental features
